A nine-year-old boy stole the show after he freestyled his own routine at a school performance. The lad is seen breaking out in his own moves before joining in with the rest of his classmates – and he has now even been praised by actor Kevin Bacon for dancing to his own tune. Lindsey Woodhurst, 30, captured the video of her son, Tripp Thomure, entertaining the audience. She said: ‘He likes to show off his dance moves! ‘Tripp is so original and the video really shows his personality. ‘He lives life to the fullest.’ The clip has amassed an incredible 8 million views on TikTok, with more than half a million likes and nearly 7,500 comments. Lindsey, from Perry in Missouri, described the online reaction as ‘amazing’ and said Tripp is loving his internet fame. ‘He’s always wanted to be TikTok famous and now he’s going to get it done! ‘So many commenters have said how funny he is. ‘People online have been encouraging him to just keep being himself.’ Tripp has even got attention from celebrities, with star of Footloose Kevin Bacon posting: ‘Nothing to be ashamed of, just some great moves.’ Marissa Weber posted in reply: ‘Footloose approves, nothing more needs to be said.’ Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. For more stories like this, check our news page.